The paper focuses on the construction of suffix trees, which is a fundamental data structure in string processing and text indexing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the practical implementation of the algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The empirical evaluation of the algorithm suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
